{
  "texts": [
    "Recent advancements in Large Language Models (LLMs) have showcased their impressive reasoning, planning, and problem-solving capabilities across various tasks (Chiang et al., 2023; OpenAI, 2023b; Ouyang et al., 2022; Wei et al., 2022; Yao et al., 2023).",
    "LLMs augmented with memory, belief, and tools have excelled in multi-step reasoning and outperformed state-of-the-art reinforcement learning methods in open-domain survival games and simple two-player imperfect information games (Park et al., 2023; Huang et al., 2022; Guo et al., 2023).",
    "Researchers have also explored multi-agent coordination using unreal benchmark environments (Carroll et al., 2019; Wang et al., 2022; Agashe et al., 2023; Li et al., 2023c) and studied human collaborative behaviors (Riedl et al., 2021).",
    "However, using LLMs to investigate collaborative behaviors in imperfect information games, especially in the Chinese environment, remains largely unexplored.",
    "Our research focuses on integrating theoryof-mind (ToM) capabilities into the planning process in Guandan, leveraging LLMs' zero-shot capabilities and ability to facilitate natural language interactions, which is lacking in other studies."
  ]
}